2.Name: image
2.Label: Image
2.Notes: A visual representation other than text. Digitised or born digital images, drawings, paintings or photographs.

3.Name: lexicalResource
3.Label: Lexical Resource
3.Notes: A set of structured items describing or defining various aspects of lexical units (words, multi-word expressions).

4.Name: controlledVocabulary
4.Label: Controlled Vocabulary
4.Notes: An organised set of terms to provide a consistent way to describe data. Examples include subject headings, taxonomies, thesauri, and ontologies.

5.Name: workflow
5.Label: Workflow
5.Notes: A structured series of steps which can be executed to (re-)produce a final outcome.

6.Name: recordingSession
6.Label: Recording Session
6.Notes: A bundle of resources capturing different aspects of a recording, usually an audio or video file with a transcription and metadata describing the characteristics of the recording.

7.Name: tei
7.Label: XML/TEI
7.Notes: A text that is encoded according to the TEI guidelines.

8.Name: collection
8.Label: Collection
8.Notes: An aggregation of resources of various types. If a collection consists of a single type, use the single type to describe it.

10.Name: grammar
10.Label: Grammar
10.Notes: A formalized description of the structure of a language.

11.Name: software
11.Label: Software
11.Notes: A computer program in source code (text) or compiled form.

12.Name: dataset
12.Label: Dataset
12.Notes: Data encoded in a defined structure. Could be data from measurements.

14.Name: audioVisual
14.Label: Audio Visual
14.Notes: A series of visual representations imparting an impression of motion when shown in succession. May or may not include sound. May be used for films, video etc.

16.Name: sound
16.Label: Sound
16.Notes: A resource primarily intended to be heard.  E. g. an audio recording.

18.Name: physicalObject
18.Label: Physical Object
18.Notes: An inanimate, three-dimensional object or substance. E. g. an artefact.

19.Name: text
19.Label: Text
19.Notes: A resource consisting primarily of words for reading.

20.Name: model
20.Label: Model
20.Notes: An abstract, conceptual, graphical, mathematical or visualisation model that represents empirical objects, phenomena, or physical processes. Modelled descriptions of, for example, different aspects of languages or a molecular biology reaction chain.

21.Name: corpus
21.Label: Corpus
21.Notes: A body of data of one kind (text or audio) that can be accessed and analysed as a whole, usually via a corpus search system; corpus is in general not synonymous with or narrower than a collection, because the individual items may not be accessible separately.

22.Name: other
22.Label: Other
22.Notes: Choose only in case none of the other resource types applies.

23.Name: service
23.Label: Service
23.Notes: A system that provides one or more functions of value to the end-user.

25.Name: interactiveResource
25.Label: Interactive Resource
25.Notes: A resource requiring interaction from the user to be understood, executed, or experienced. Files that require use of a viewer or query/response portals.

28.Name: computationalNotebook
28.Label: Computational Notebook
28.Notes: A virtual notebook environment used for literate programming.

29.Name: annotation
29.Label: Annotation
29.Notes: Additional/secondary structured information explicating certain aspects of the original resource (which could be of any type: text, audio, video, image, ...).

34.Name: georeferenced
34.Label: Georeferenced Image
34.Notes: An image that embeds georeferencing information, such as a GeoTIFF file.

39.Name: academic
39.Label: academic
39.Notes: Academic access means that an affiliation with an academic institution is checked via Shibboleth login.

40.Name: restricted
40.Label: restricted
40.Notes: Restricted access requires registration and an a permission from the owner.

41.Name: public
41.Label: public
41.Notes: Public resources are accessible without any further restrictions.

42.Name: inc
42.Label: In Copyright
42.Notes: This Rights Statement can be used for an Item that is in copyright. Using this statement implies that the organization making this Item available has determined that the Item is in copyright and either is the rights-holder, has obtained permission from the rights-holder(s) to make their Work(s) available, or makes the Item available under an exception or limitation to copyright (including Fair Use) that entitles it to make the Item available.

43.Name: noc-oklr
43.Label: No Copyright - Other Known Legal Restrictions
43.Notes: This Rights Statement should be used for Items that are in the Public Domain but that cannot be freely re-used as the consequence of known legal restrictions that prevent the organization that intends to make the Item available from allowing free re-use of the Item, such as cultural heritage or traditional cultural expression protections. In order for this Rights Statement to be conclusive, the organization that intends to make the Item available should provide a link to a page detailing the legal restrictions that limit re-use of the Item.

44.Name: cc-by-nc-nd-4-0
44.Label: Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-ND 4.0)
44.Notes: This license is the most restrictive of our six main licenses, only allowing others to download your works and share them with others as long as they credit you, but they can’t change them in any way or use them commercially.

45.Name: mit
45.Label: MIT license
45.Notes: The MIT License is a permissive free software license originating at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT). It is intended to be used for software licensing.

50.Name: cc-by-nd-4-0
50.Label: Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0 International (CC BY-ND 4.0)
50.Notes: This license lets others reuse the work for any purpose, including commercially; however, it cannot be shared with others in adapted form, and credit must be provided to you.

51.Name: cc-by-nc-sa-4-0
51.Label: Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)
51.Notes: This license lets others remix, tweak, and build upon your work non-commercially, as long as they credit you and license their new creations under the identical terms.

54.Name: cc-by-sa-4-0
54.Label: Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)
54.Notes: This license lets others remix, tweak, and build upon your work even for commercial purposes, as long as they credit you and license their new creations under the identical terms. This license is often compared to “copyleft” free and open source software licenses. All new works based on yours will carry the same license, so any derivatives will also allow commercial use. This is the license used by Wikipedia, and is recommended for materials that would benefit from incorporating content from Wikipedia and similarly licensed projects.

56.Name: inc-ow-eu
56.Label: In Copyright - EU Orphan Work
56.Notes: This Rights Statement is intended for use with Items for which the underlying Work has been identified as an Orphan Work in accordance with Directive 2012/28/EU of the European Parliament and of the Council of 25 October 2012 on certain permitted uses of Orphan Works. It can only be applied to Items derived from Works that are covered by the Directive: Works published in the form of books, journals, newspapers, magazines or other writings as well as cinematographic or audiovisual works and phonograms (note: this excludes photography and visual arts). It can only be applied by organizations that are beneficiaries of the Directive: publicly accessible libraries, educational establishments and museums, archives, film or audio heritage institutions and public-service broadcasting organizations, established in one of the EU member states. The beneficiary is also expected to have registered the work in the EU Orphan Works Database maintained by EUIPO.

57.Name: cne
57.Label: Copyright Not Evaluated
57.Notes: This Rights Statement should be used for Items for which the copyright status is unknown and for which the organization that intends to make the Item available has not undertaken an effort to determine the copyright status of the underlying Work.

59.Name: inc-edu
59.Label: In Copyright - Educational Use Permitted
59.Notes: This Rights Statement can be used only for copyrighted Items for which the organization making the Item available is the rights-holder or has been explicitly authorized by the rights-holder(s) to allow third parties to use their Work(s) for educational purposes without first obtaining permission.

60.Name: publicdomain-1-0
60.Label: Public Domain Mark 1.0
60.Notes:
This work has been identified as being free of known restrictions under copyright law, including all related and neighboring rights.
You can copy, modify, distribute and perform the work, even for commercial purposes, all without asking permission.

63.Name: noc-nc
63.Label: No Copyright - Non-Commercial Use Only
63.Notes: This Rights Statement can only be used for Works that are in the Public Domain and have been digitized in a public-private partnership as part of which, the partners have agreed to limit commercial uses of this digital representation of the Work by third parties. It has been developed specifically to allow the inclusion of Works that have been digitized as part of the partnerships between European Libraries and Google, but can in theory be applied to Items that have been digitized in similar public-private partnerships.

65.Name: cc-by-nc-4-0
65.Label: Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0)
65.Notes: This license lets others remix, tweak, and build upon your work non-commercially, and although their new works must also acknowledge you and be non-commercial, they don’t have to license their derivative works on the same terms.

69.Notes:

You can copy, modify, distribute and perform the work, even for commercial purposes, all without asking permission.

73.Name: cc-by-4-0
73.Label: Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
73.Notes: This license lets others distribute, remix, tweak, and build upon your work, even commercially, as long as they credit you for the original creation. This is the most accommodating of licenses offered. Recommended for maximum dissemination and use of licensed materials.

76.Name: deprecated
76.Label: deprecated
76.Notes: If an object is deprecated it is not longer actively worked on and it might not be complete.

77.Name: active
77.Label: active
77.Notes: Active indicates an actively worked on object.

78.Name: completed
78.Label: completed
78.Notes: A complete object is not longer worked on and results are final.

79.Name: clarin-vlo
79.Label: CLARIN VLO
79.Notes:
Denotes Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by the CLARIN Virtual Language Observatory (VLO, https://vlo.clarin.eu).
Criteria for inclusion: the object should be a language resource, i. e. conform to the criteria defined by the Class E33 'Linguistic Object' in CIDOC CRM.
From the definition of E33: the set comprises identifiable expressions in natural language or languages. Instances can be expressed in many ways: e.g. as written texts, recorded speech or sign language. They are independent from the medium or method by which they are expressed. Expressions in formal languages, such as computer code or mathematical formulae, are not part of the set. (http://www.cidoc-crm.org/Entity/e33-linguistic-object/version-6.1)
Examples: a photograph of an inscription, a text document, a scan of a text document, a dictionary file, a corpus, an audio recording etc.

81.Name: kulturpool
81.Label: Kulturpool
81.Notes:
Denotes any Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by Kulturpool (http://www.kulturpool.at) which is further harvested by Europeana (https://www.europeana.eu). 
To have a better understanding of what should be included, have a look at the Europeana Content Strategy (https://pro.europeana.eu/post/europeana-content-strategy).
Criteria for inlcusion: relation to cultural heritage, high-quality content, open data (metadata has to point to a freely accessible digital object), relation to Europe.

82.Name: ariadne
82.Label: ARIADNE
82.Notes:
Denotes any Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by ARIADNEplus (https://ariadne-infrastructure.eu).
Criteria for inclusion: relation to archaeology, e.g. hasRelatedDiscipline is 6010 or one of subcategories in ÖFOS 2012 (https://vocabs.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/oefosdisciplines/6010).

83.Name: openaire_data
83.Label: OpenAIRE
83.Notes:
Denotes any Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by the OpenAIRE (https://www.openaire.eu/).
Criteria for inclusion: all top collections.

84.Name: clarin-fcs
84.Label: CLARIN-FCS
84.Notes:
Denotes any Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be aggregated by the CLARIN Federated Content Search (https://www.clarin.eu/content/federated-content-search-clarin-fcs).
Criteria for inclusion: full text searchable resources
